            <description>Introduction

The size of astronomical datasets has increased dramatically over the years; terabyte sized datasets are no longer an exception. This trend will only accelerate; the SKA is expected to produce nearly 1 TB of archived data each day. This means that it will no longer be feasible for astronomers to download these huge datasets and perform the data reduction on their own machines, as is currently the practice. Instead the data reduction is likely to be done close to where the data is a…</description>
